   }
   ```
   This modification makes the condition `i + n`, which is always true (non-zero) for `i = 0` and `n = 3`. The loop will run indefinitely.

5. Replace "i--" with "n--":
   ```c++
   for (int i = 0; i < n; n--) {
       cout << '$';
   }
   ```
   This modification decrements `n` instead of `i`. The loop will execute 3 times, printing "$$$".

6. Replace "cout << '$'" with "cout << "$$$"":
   ```c++
   for (int i = 0; i < n; i--) {
